## 11. DATA INTEGRITY PARITY TESTS

These tests verify that Android writes match iOS expectations at the DB level.

| ID | Scenario | DB Assertion |
|---|---|---|
| DI1 | Book a free game | `bookings.status='confirmed'`, `fee_paid=false`, `payment_method IS NULL` |
| DI2 | Book a paid game (card) | `bookings.status='confirmed'`, `fee_paid=true`, `payment_method='stripe'`, `stripe_payment_intent_id NOT NULL` |
| DI3 | Book with full credit cover | `bookings.status='confirmed'`, `fee_paid=false`, `payment_method IS NULL`, `credits_applied_cents = totalFee` |
| DI4 | Cancel inside 6h window | `bookings.status='cancelled'`, `cancellation_reason='player_cancelled'`; no new `credit_transactions` row |
| DI5 | Cancel outside 6h window | `bookings.status='cancelled'`; new `credit_transactions` row with `reason='cancellation_refund'`; `player_credits.amount_cents` incremented |
| DI6 | UUID in all PostgREST filters | All `user_id`, `club_id`, `game_id` values in queries are lowercase | `data_contracts.me §5` |
| DI7 | Timestamp decode | All `created_at`, `date_time`, `hold_expires_at` decode to correct `Instant` without null | `data_contracts.me §4` |
| DI8 | Credit balance never negative | `player_credits.amount_cents >= 0` after any deduction | `backend_authority.me §2` |

